summary: SummaryLancôme Absolue The Eye Cream Is a luxurious anti-aging eye cream that helps to visibly improve 6 eye parameters; including crow's feet, wrinkles around the eyes, and under-eye bags.
details: DetailsBenefitsAbsolue The Eye Cream helps to target aging signs for visibly younger-looking eyes.Formulated with a new exclusive ingredient, a Peptide created using biotechnology, in combination with Perpetual Rose Extract and Proxylane, this luxurious anti aging eye cream helps to visibly reduce multiple forms of wrinkles and smooth the eye contour.Within hours, skin elasticity and firmness are improved, and the eye area is moisturized with hydration lasting up to 24-hours.In 4 weeks, see visible improvement on eye wrinkles including crow's feet, under-eye wrinkles, wrinkles between the eyes, and reduced appearance of under-eye bags.Key IngredientsBiotech Peptide: A new ingredient in Absolue that was discovered with support of Artificial Intelligence and created through a biotech process. This ingredient is a peptide molecule that has wrinkle smoothing benefits.Perpetual Rose Extract: Exclusive to Lancôme, this rose is grown on the Plateau Valensole in the South of France and is hand harvested with care in the early morning.Proxylane: Developed by L'Oréal and originally derived from sugar, it is known to help increase skin firmness and tone.Research ResultsClinical Results: Visibly Improve 6 Eye Parameters In 4 WeeksUnder Eye Bags -26.91%; Under Eye Wrinkles -19.75%Wrinkles Between Eyes (Glabellar) -17.63%; Crow’s Feet Wrinkles -16.5%Fine Lines -7%; Smoothness +5%*Based on clinical testing on 53 women after 4 weeks*Based on clinical testing on 41 women after 4 weeksItem 2630545How To UseFor best results, use this anti aging eye cream daily in the morning and at night. Apply as the last step in your routine.Step 1: Take a small amount of product and warm between fingertips.Step 2: Using your fingertips, dab several small pearls of the cream to the delicate skin under the eye and onto the brow bone.Step 3: Gently smooth the cream into the eye contour, moving from inner to outer corners. Avoid pulling the skin or applying too closely to the eyes.Step 4: Using two fingers, smooth the outer eye area followed by the area between the eyes, using upward motions.Step 5: Repeat each stroke 3 times until the product is fully absorbed.IngredientsAqua / Water / Eau, Glycerin, Rosa Damascena Flower Water, Butylene Glycol, Butyrospermum Parkii Butter / Shea Butter, Jojoba Esters, Dimethicone, Isopropyl Myristate, Peg/Ppg/Polybutylene Glycol-8/5/3 Glycerin, Peg-40 Stearate, Isopropyl Isostearate, Helianthus Annuus Seed Cera / Sunflower Seed Wax, Cera Alba / Beeswax / Cire Dabeille, Glyceryl Stearate, Peg-100 Stearate, Propanediol, Stearyl Alcohol, Hydroxypropyl Tetrahydropyrantriol, Octyldodecanol, Escin, Rosa Centifolia Flower Extract, Rosa Hybrid Flower Extract, Adenosine, Capryloyl Salicylic Acid, Hydrolyzed Linseed Extract, Hydroxyacetophenone, Pentaerythrityl Tetra-Di-T-Butyl Hydroxyhydrocinnamate, Saccharomyces Ferment Filtrate• Sodium Hydroxide •Trisodium Ethylenediamine Disuccinate, Panthenol• Tocopherol, Acacia Decurrens Flower Cera / Acacia Decurrens Flower Wax, Polyglycerin-3, Acrylamide/Sodium Acryloyldimethyltaurate Copolymer• Alcohol, Ammonium Polyacryloyldimethyl Taurate, Arginine, CI 77891 /Titanium Dioxide, Citric Acid, Isohexadecane, Maltodextrin, Mica, Peg-20 Stearate, Polysorbate 80, Propylene Glycol, Rosa Damascena Flower Oil, Sorbitan Oleate, Sorbitan Tristearate, Tin Oxide, Dimethiconol, Polysilicone-11, Citronellol, Geraniol, CI 19140 / Yellow 5, CI 77491 / Iron Oxides, Phenoxyethanol, Salicylic Acid, Sodium Benzoate.Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details

faceoff_positive.comments: I was graciously gifted the Absolue Eye Cream from Loreal and BzzAgent for my honest opinion so here it is. This stuff is an absolute GODSEND and I'm not even exaggerating a little. It completely transformed my undereyes in 6 DAYS after a major crisis before I had to attend an important event that I was adamant that I wouldn't miss. If you only knew what my eyes and undereyes (as well as my nose, and chin when I realized that I had MRSA which I had spread not realizing THAT is what it was that was making this disaster) looked like when my undereyes normally were basically fairly wrinkle free, you would have buried yourself underground and never showed your face. My eyes alone looked like I had aged 60+ years just from having to gently try to pull down my eyelids MULTIPLE x's/day to do a 'clean out sess' of the infection gunk that kept flooding around my eyeballs and settling in my eyelids. I always still applied my normal eye cream under my eyes after to try to retain moisture and prevent the stretching of the skin too much. But by the time I had the MRSA completely gone, the only thing left to show for it was the 80+ year old looking eye wrinkles staring back at me. I now had 6 days before my nieces event that I wouldn't, I couldn't miss, but my gosh every time I looked in the mirror all I wanted to do is curl up in bed and throw away the key because I thought, this is going to be an IMPOSSIBLE feat! My normal eye cream didn't help keep them from wrinkling so I had to try something new. I remembered that I was gifted what turned out to be my blessing in disguise th Absolue Eye Cream by Loreal. I  applied it religiously every single day morning and night and sometimes even a few times during the day since my skin had gotten extremely dehydrated from the MRSA treatment. Now came the day of my nieces event and my eyes looked like NOTHING happened and were actually BETTER than before. Many said I look like I'm in my 20's (I'm 45). I LOVE this stuff and you will you!
faceoff_positive.headline: This is an ABSOLU(T)E miracle

faceoff_negative.comments:
While it offers promising benefits for the delicate eye area, it didn't entirely meet my expectations due to its slight greasiness.

Pros:
 Upon application, the cream feels rich and hydrating, which is ideal for combatting dryness around the eyes. I noticed an immediate plumping effect, which helped diminish fine lines temporarily. The formula includes notable ingredients like hyaluronic acid and vitamin E, known for their moisturizing and antioxidant properties.

Cons:
Despite its moisturizing benefits, I found the cream to be a bit greasier than I prefer for daytime use. It tends to leave a subtle sheen on the skin that might not sit well under makeup or in humid climates. For those with oily skin or who prefer a matte finish, this aspect could be a drawback.

Overall Impression:
Delivers on its promise of hydration and anti-aging benefits. However, its greasy texture might not suit everyone's preferences, particularly those looking for a lightweight eye cream for daytime wear. I would recommend it more for evening use or during colder months when extra moisture is beneficial and the sheen is less noticeable.
faceoff_negative.headline: Probably a pass for me
